name: White Label Churchill
additionalNotes: 6 years of aging has mellowed their taste and made these Churchills into the smoothest and best tasting Don Kiki cigar. They are mild and have a well-rounded and complex taste. Exquisite sun grown and extremely aged long-filler virgin Cuban-Seed Habano tobacco from the 1999 harvest is combined with a flawless Connecticut wrapper that was shade-grown in Ecuador.
